abovegrade

Waiting for minutes, sometimes tens of minutes, after a bus or train was scheduled to arrive has become an all too familiar experience for public transit riders in the United States.

Combined with the effects of the COVID-19 pandemic, this persistent lack of reliability stands as a significant obstacle to public transit use. To address this problem, governments and transit agencies need to know where public transit is least reliable so as to target resources accordingly.

Abovegrade.org uses publicly available transit datasets to create key reliability metrics evaluating transportation services in Philadelphia.

Agencies and passengers use abovegrade.org to understand the transit landscape of their city to identify its problems, guide policy, and deliver better services.
